{
  "texts": [
    "Ultimately, the considered TSK-FRBS has 3573 parameters overall.In the case of TSK-FRBS, a measure of feature importance can be obtained by averaging the absolute values of the coefficients of the linear models in the rule base.",
    "Formally, the importance I of the feature j is evaluated as follows:I (T SK) j = 1 N rule • N rule r =1 |γ r, j | ∀ j ∈ {1,..., M}.",
    "(11)where γ r, j is the coefficient for the variable j in the rule r. Figure 10 suggests that feature importance computed for the TSK-FRBS model is consistent with the one computed for the MLP-NN by the SHAP method in the IID setting.",
    "Age and test_time are identified as the most and the least relevant features, respectively.",
    "Furthermore, the importance of HNR and DFA is similar, consistently with what is observed for the MLP-NN.A direct comparison of the importance values between Fig. 8 (MLP-NN) and 10 (TSK-FRBS) is not meaningful."
  ]
}